{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_44","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"curl -sL --retry 2 --connect-timeout 10 'https://www.ebi.ac.uk/europepmc/webservices/rest/search?query=EXT_ID:8321236%20AND%20SRC:MED&format=json&resultType=core' | head -c 6000\"","aggregated_output":"{\"version\":\"6.9\",\"hitCount\":1,\"request\":{\"queryString\":\"EXT_ID:8321236 AND SRC:MED\",\"internalQuery\":\"EXT_ID:8321236 AND SRC:MED\",\"resultType\":\"CORE\",\"cursorMark\":\"*\",\"pageSize\":25,\"sort\":\"\",\"synonym\":false},\"resultList\":{\"result\":[{\"id\":\"8321236\",\"source\":\"MED\",\"pmid\":\"8321236\",\"pmcid\":\"PMC359993\",\"fullTextIdList\":{\"fullTextId\":[\"PMC359993\"]},\"doi\":\"10.1128/mcb.13.7.4342-4350.1993\",\"title\":\"The fission yeast ferric reductase gene frp1+ is required for ferric iron uptake and encodes a protein that is homologous to the gp91-phox subunit of the human NADPH phagocyte oxidoreductase.\",\"authorString\":\"Roman DG, Dancis A, Anderson GJ, Klausner RD.\",\"authorList\":{\"author\":[{\"fullName\":\"Roman DG\",\"firstName\":\"D G\",\"lastName\":\"Roman\",\"initials\":\"DG\",\"authorAffiliationDetailsList\":{\"authorAffiliation\":[{\"affiliation\":\"Cell Biology and Metabolism Branch, National Institute of Child Health and Human Development, Bethesda, Maryland 20892.\"}]}},{\"fullName\":\"Dancis A\",\"firstName\":\"A\",\"lastName\":\"Dancis\",\"initials\":\"A\"},{\"fullName\":\"Anderson GJ\",\"firstName\":\"G J\",\"lastName\":\"Anderson\",\"initials\":\"GJ\",\"authorId\":{\"type\":\"ORCID\",\"value\":\"0000-0002-8814-5866\"}},{\"fullName\":\"Klausner RD\",\"firstName\":\"R D\",\"lastName\":\"Klausner\",\"initials\":\"RD\"}]},\"authorIdList\":{\"authorId\":[{\"type\":\"ORCID\",\"value\":\"0000-0002-8814-5866\"}]},\"dataLinksTagsList\":{\"dataLinkstag\":[\"related_data\"]},\"journalInfo\":{\"issue\":\"7\",\"volume\":\"13\",\"journalIssueId\":689684,\"dateOfPublication\":\"1993 Jul\",\"monthOfPublication\":7,\"yearOfPublication\":1993,\"printPublicationDate\":\"1993-07-01\",\"journal\":{\"title\":\"Molecular and cellular biology\",\"medlineAbbreviation\":\"Mol Cell Biol\",\"nlmid\":\"8109087\",\"isoabbreviation\":\"Mol Cell Biol\",\"issn\":\"0270-7306\",\"essn\":\"1098-5549\"}},\"pubYear\":\"1993\",\"pageInfo\":\"4342-4350\",\"abstractText\":\"We have identified a cell surface ferric reductase activity in the fission yeast Schizosaccharomyces pombe. A mutant strain deficient in this activity was also deficient in ferric iron uptake, while ferrous iron uptake was not impaired. Therefore, reduction is a required step in cellular ferric iron acquisition. We have cloned frp1+, the wild-type allele of the mutant gene. frp1+ mRNA levels were repressed by iron addition to the growth medium. Fusion of 138 nucleotides of frp1+ promoter sequences to a reporter gene, the bacterial chloramphenicol acetyltransferase gene, conferred iron-dependent regulation upon the latter when introduced into S. pombe. The predicted amino acid sequence of the frp1+ gene exhibits hydrophobic regions compatible with transmembrane domains. It shows similarity to the Saccharomyces cerevisiae FRE1 gene product and the gp91-phox protein, a component of the human NADPH phagocyte oxidoreductase that is deficient in X-linked chronic granulomatous disease.\",\"affiliation\":\"Cell Biology and Metabolism Branch, National Institute of Child Health and Human Development, Bethesda, Maryland 20892.\",\"publicationStatus\":\"ppublish\",\"language\":\"eng\",\"pubModel\":\"Print\",\"pubTypeList\":{\"pubType\":[\"research-article\",\"Journal Article\"]},\"meshHeadingList\":{\"meshHeading\":[{\"majorTopic_YN\":\"N\",\"descriptorName\":\"Phagocytes\",\"meshQualifierList\":{\"meshQualifier\":[{\"abbreviation\":\"EN\",\"qualifierName\":\"enzymology\",\"majorTopic_YN\":\"N\"}]}},{\"majorTopic_YN\":\"N\",\"descriptorName\":\"Animals\"},{\"majorTopic_YN\":\"N\",\"descriptorName\":\"Cattle\"},{\"majorTopic_YN\":\"N\",\"descriptorName